  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Caribbean Response Preparedness and Resilience Programme (Anguilla, BVI and TCI) is the second phase of the Hurricane Irma and Maria Response Programme in these territories.
&#xC2;&#xA0;
The programme aims to strengthen the capacity of local Red Cross Branches in the British Overseas Territories (OTs) of Turks &amp; Caicos Islands (TCI), British Virgin Islands (BVI) and Anguilla to better support people in crises during disasters.
&#xC2;</narrative>
  </description>
